# Sales Portal — Cursor Rules

## Project overview
Next.js 14 App Router + Tailwind CSS + TypeScript sales portal.
No database — all persistence is JSON files in /data/.
Built for handoff to R&D; keep code clean and replaceable.

## Architecture
- /data/users.json — all users, passwords (plain text for now), permissions
- /data/config.json — buttons, prompts, AI settings, app settings
- /lib/data.ts — all file read/write (server-only)
- /lib/session.ts — base64 cookie session (intentionally simple for handoff)
- /middleware.ts — route protection
- /app/api/ — all API routes (server-side only)
- /app/login/ — public login page
- /app/portal/ — salesperson view
- /app/admin/ — admin-only section

## Core rules

### Never hardcode
- No hardcoded prompts in components or API routes
- No hardcoded button labels, IDs, or configs
- No hardcoded API keys — always read from config.json via /api/config
- All user-facing text that admins should control lives in config.json

### Data persistence
- All config changes go through PUT /api/config
- All user changes go through /api/users or /api/users/[id]
- Always read config fresh from API, never cache in a module-level variable
- After any mutation, reload data from the API (not local state patch)

### Auth & permissions
- Session is a base64 cookie (sp_session) — simple and intentional
- Never trust client-side role/permission checks for actual data
- API routes must validate session server-side before every operation
- Admin routes check role === "admin" on every request
- Portal buttons are filtered by user.permissions array (button IDs)

### Design system
- Use only CSS classes defined in globals.css: btn-primary, btn-secondary, btn-ghost, btn-destructive, input-field, card, label
- Color via Tailwind tokens only: bg-background, text-foreground, text-muted-foreground, border-border, etc.
- Font weight 300 is default body, 400 for headings — never bold unless intentional
- No arbitrary Tailwind values unless absolutely necessary
- Spacing: px-4 py-2 for most elements, gap-2 or gap-3 for layouts

### Component patterns
- Portal: single page, left sidebar nav, main content area changes based on active button — no routing
- Admin: each section is its own page under /admin/[section]
- Forms: inline (no modal) — show/hide with state, not navigation
- Loading states: small spinner (w-4 h-4 rounded-full border-2 border-primary border-t-transparent animate-spin)
- Errors: text-xs text-destructive inline below the relevant field

### TypeScript
- Type all API responses
- Prefer interfaces over types for objects
- No any unless genuinely necessary

### File mutations
- When modifying a JSON config section (e.g. buttons), always fetch the full config first, spread it, replace only the changed section, then PUT the whole config back
- Never partially update config — always write the complete object

## What NOT to do
- Do not add a database
- Do not add NextAuth or any auth library
- Do not add new npm packages without checking if something in the existing stack works
- Do not add dark mode toggle UI (dark mode CSS is defined but not user-toggled for now)
- Do not create separate CSS files — all styles go in globals.css or as Tailwind classes
- Do not create new API routes for things already handled by /api/config (PUT the whole config)

## Adding new features
When adding a new portal button/tool:
1. Add a prompt in admin → Prompts
2. Add a button in admin → Buttons, link to the prompt
3. Grant button ID to relevant users in admin → Users
No code changes needed.

When adding a new admin section:
1. Create /app/admin/[section]/page.tsx
2. Add nav item in /app/admin/layout.tsx navItems array
3. Read/write via /api/config or new /api/[resource] route following existing patterns
